{"priority": "trivial", "kind": "bug", "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/levitsky/biolccc.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/levitsky/biolccc"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{2a53826d-c82d-4189-a154-b404d844ef71}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "biolccc", "full_name": "levitsky/biolccc", "uuid": "{2a53826d-c82d-4189-a154-b404d844ef71}"}, "links": {"attachments": {"href": "data/repositories/levitsky/biolccc/issues/1/attachments_page=1.json"}, "self": {"href": "data/repositories/levitsky/biolccc/issues/1.json"}, "watch": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/levitsky/biolccc/issues/1/watch"}, "comments": {"href": "data/repositories/levitsky/biolccc/issues/1/comments_page=1.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/levitsky/biolccc/issues/1/memory-leaks"}, "vote": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/levitsky/biolccc/issues/1/vote"}}, "reporter": {"display_name": "Dennis Goldfarb", "uuid": "{ac62458c-48d5-479c-8cd4-ee06ddb3a74c}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bac62458c-48d5-479c-8cd4-ee06ddb3a74c%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bac62458c-48d5-479c-8cd4-ee06ddb3a74c%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f65cd2dec2a57793ed005033cf8b41c7d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsDG-2.png"}}, "nickname": "dennisgoldfarb", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:e1a27004-1238-49cf-a5ce-8c41c7b1f09b"}, "title": "Memory leaks", "component": null, "votes": 0, "watches": 3, "content": {"raw": "Hi, I found a couple memory leaks in BioLCCC.\r\n\r\nIn auxiliary.cpp\r\n\r\n1) in function fitPolynomial: double * matrix = new double[n*n]; \r\nmatrix doesn't have a corresponding delete[] at the end of the function\r\n\r\n2) in function fitSpline: delete[] c1, d1; \r\nthis needs to be written as delete[] c1; delete[] d1;\r\nSilly C++. Here's a quick explanation http://stackoverflow.com/questions/6694745/how-to-delete-multiple-dynamically-allocated-arrays-in-a-single-delete-statement", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Hi, I found a couple memory leaks in BioLCCC.</p>\n<p>In auxiliary.cpp</p>\n<p>1) in function fitPolynomial: double * matrix = new double[n*n]; \nmatrix doesn't have a corresponding delete[] at the end of the function</p>\n<p>2) in function fitSpline: delete[] c1, d1; \nthis needs to be written as delete[] c1; delete[] d1;\nSilly C++. Here's a quick explanation <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/6694745/how-to-delete-multiple-dynamically-allocated-arrays-in-a-single-delete-statement\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">http://stackoverflow.com/questions/6694745/how-to-delete-multiple-dynamically-allocated-arrays-in-a-single-delete-statement</a></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": {"display_name": "Anton Goloborodko", "uuid": "{cab0d15d-6748-4ce8-8aa7-26f698229092}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bcab0d15d-6748-4ce8-8aa7-26f698229092%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bcab0d15d-6748-4ce8-8aa7-26f698229092%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/account/golobor/avatar/"}}, "nickname": "golobor", "type": "user", "account_id": null}, "state": "new", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2015-08-18T18:57:10.995896+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2015-08-18T19:25:42.091983+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 1}